"'''The League of Spies''',"<ref name="TERC" /><ref name="Insider73">[[Star Wars Insider 73|''Star Wars Insider'' 73]]</ref> its title also presented as "'''The Clone Wars: League of Spies''',"<ref name="Insider73" /> is a short story written by [[Aaron Allston]] that was originally published in [[Star Wars Insider 73|''Star Wars Insider'' 73]]. In [[March]] [[2008]], it was archived on [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]]. It was also included in a Czech-language anthology ''[[Setkání v mlze]]''.

==Plot summary==
In the midst of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], a [[Republic Intelligence/Legends|Republic Intelligence]] [[Agent/Legends|agent]] called [[Edbit Teeks]] goes missing on the world of [[Tarhassan]], which has recently declared itself for the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]]. A team of newly-recruited agents is sent to rescue him, but their inexperience starts to threaten the entire mission and it comes down to [[Joram Kithe]] to save the day.

